COMMENT: Employer Identification Number, a unique identification number that is assigned to a business by the IRS.
Unique identifier assigned by Cybersyn to each company.
The exchange code for the primary trading venue of a security.
Permanent Identifier, which is a identifier provided by Refinitiv (via PermID) to provide a way to uniquely identify a company.
Central Index Key, a unique identifier for corporations registered with the United States Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC).
Describes the type or level of the entity for additional convenience. Currently, all entities are corporate entities and are denoted as 'Corporate'.
The exchange name for the primary trading venue of a security.
Legal Entity Identifier, a unique identifier from GLEIF that identifies legal entities that engage in financial transactions.
An array of ticker symbols under which the security may be traded globally on all exchanges.
The ticker for the primary trading venue of a security. If a security trades on multiple exchanges or has numerous tickers, an attempt is made to select the ticker from the home market.
